15
[p 
	"Rockman movie. Completed in the length of 16:57.93 at October 2nd, 2005.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"It is 1:23 (83 seconds) faster than the previously submitted Rockman movie.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The making of this movie, which is v6 in my personal numbering,
	$LF
	"started in February 2005 when Finalfighter contacted me and
	$LF
	"demonstrated a ceiling-jump-wrap trick, which you will see
	$LF
	"near the end of the Cutman stage.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Before that, I was making v5, very slowly, in hopes that I will
	$LF
	"somehow be able to improve v4 by about 5 seconds.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Soon thereafter, I found out that it's actually possible to get
	$LF
	"the Magnet Beam from the Elecman stage without possessing either
	$LF
	"the Hyper Arm (Gutsman's weapon) or the Elec Beam (Elecman's weapon).
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"I did some testing, and found out that despite the fact that Elecman's
	$LF
	"killing takes tons of time with the regular weapon, the gain gotten
	$LF
	"by using Magnet Beam in the Gutsman stage still outweighs this loss.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Enough of the memories. Here are the plain numbers:
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" Elecman stage: Lost 781 frames.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" In the stage, I 
				[em 
					"gained
				]em
				" 520 frames, but in the boss, I lost 1281 frames because I only had the regular weapon.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
		" Iceman stage: Gained 524 frames.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Fireman stage: Gained 274 frames.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Bombman stage: Gained 368 frames.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Gutsman stage: Gained 1811 frames. This outbalanced the loss from the Elecman stage.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Cutman stage: Gained 380 frames.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Between-levels: Gained about 90 frames.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Wily1: Gained 296 frames.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Wily2, Wily3, Wily4: Not precisely measured.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
